Reasoning: The paper presents a theory of environmental bisimilarity for the delimited-control operators shift and reset, which are commonly used in programming languages and formal methods. This makes the paper relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including programming languages (cs.PL), logic in computer science (cs.LO), software engineering (cs.SE), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), and language and automata theory (cs.LG).
